<title>UK: BBA H1 pretax up 19 pct post exceptionals.</title>
<headline>BBA H1 pretax up 19 pct post exceptionals.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1996-09-04</dateline>
<text>
<p>Half-year to June 30</p>
<p>			   (million stg unless stated)</p>
<p> Shr (pence) adjusted   10.3		   vs 8.3</p>
<p> Dividend (pence)	 2.1		    vs 1.8</p>
<p> Pretax		     83.1		   vs 33.8</p>
<p> Exceptional		11.0		   vs 26.7</p>
<p> Pretax pre-excep	 72.1		   vs 60.5</p>
<p> Turnover		   552.4		  vs 445.2</p>
<p>NOTE - Analysts' forecasts on pre-tax profits were in a range of 68.8 to 72.5 million stg.  </p>
<p> Operating profit	 74.5		   vs 54.9</p>
<p> Interest payable	 3.3		    vs 4.5</p>
<p> Tax			  26.8		   vs 32.4</p>
<p> Net taxed		  56.3		   vs 1.4</p>
<p> Attributable	     51.8		   vs 2.6 loss</p>
<p> Pay date		   November 15</p>
<p>Div registration date  September 24 NOTE - BBA Group Plc said it sees considerable potential to expand its core engineering business both organically and through &quot;bolt-on&quot; acquisitions. -- London Newsroom +44 171 542 7717.</p>
</text>
